File: Mr Price. (eNCA) JOHANNESBURG - Cash-strapped consumers looking for value in their clothing shopping have given Mr Price a boost in sales. Although the retail group has warned of an increase in cost pressures for the rest of the year, it says it has attracted bargain hunters. Full-year profits were up by 20 percent. Mr Price’s clothing division grew its sales by 30 percent. Meanwhile, the group’s store footprint grew to 1,721 with the acquisition of seven Yuppiechef stores.